<article>
    <h1>SA&#x2019;s re&#xAD;cent is&#xAD;sues</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200827/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-27"><time>2020-08-27</time></a>
        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>AU­GUST 2019</p>
    <p>Dis­pute with two-time SEA Games marathon cham­pion Soh Rui Yong over his non-se­lec­tion for last year’s Games in the Philip­pines, lead­ing to an on­go­ing civil suit.</p>
    <p>NOVEM­BER 2019</p>
    <p>Pays na­tional pole vaulter Rachel Yang a five-fig­ure sum af­ter ad­mit­ting that she was “pro­vided with in­for­ma­tion which was con­fus­ing” and led to her be­ing un­able to com­pete at the 2018 Asian Games in Jakarta.</p>
    <p>DE­CEM­BER 2019</p>
    <p>Dis­agree­ments re­port­edly emerge among coaches, par­ents and ath­letes com­pet­ing in the SEA Games re­lays af­ter con­fu­sion over se­lec­tion cri­te­ria. Mar­garet Oh abruptly re­signs as coach of top sprinter Shanti Pereira dur­ing the Games. She was also then in charge of the mixed 4x100m re­lay team.</p>
    <p>SA is crit­i­cised by Sin­ga­pore</p>
    <p>Sport In­sti­tute chief of high per­for­mance Richard Gor­don for its poor per­for­mance af­ter its three bronze re­sult – down from two golds, two sil­vers and four bronzes in 2017 and 3-3-3 in 2015.</p>
    <p>Na­tional re­lay coaches Melvin Tan and Hamkah Afik re­sign, with Tan cit­ing “ex­ter­nal in­ter­fer­ence” while the lat­ter felt he “could not progress in the cur­rent sit­u­a­tion”.</p>
    <p>MARCH 2020</p>
    <p>Vice-pres­i­dent (fi­nance and part­ner­ship) Poh Seng Song and ath­letes’ com­mis­sion rep­re­sen­ta­tive Gary Yeo re­sign, cit­ing dif­fer­ing opin­ions and de­ci­sions that they did not agree with.</p>
    <p>JULY 2020</p>
    <p>Pro­posed changes to its con­sti­tu­tion, to be tabled at the July 13 ex­tra­or­di­nary gen­eral meet­ing, sparks con­cern among some af­fil­i­ates. The meet­ing fails to pass two pro­posed amend­ments – re­moval of vot­ing rights for the ath­letes’ com­mis­sion rep­re­sen­ta­tive and to keep pro­ceed­ings in man­age­ment com­mit­tee meet­ings con­fi­den­tial.</p>


